'''Tomás Leandro Aranda''' (born 9 May 2007) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder (association football)|midfielder]] for [[Argentine Primera División]] club [[Boca Juniors]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]].

== Club career ==

Born in [[Ciudadela, Buenos Aires|Ciudadela]] just outside of [[Buenos Aires]], Aranda grew up in [[Villa Udaondo]], where he played for [[Club Atlético Ituzaingó]], before joining [[Boca Juniors]] in 2018.<ref name="udr">{{Cite web |date=2026-02-01 |title=Tomás Aranda, el pibe de Ciudadela que debutó y cambió las cosas en Boca |url=https://www.udr.com.ar/tomas-aranda-el-pibe-de-ciudadela-que-debuto-y-cambio-las-cosas-en-boca/ |access-date=2026-04-08 |website=UDR |language=es}}</ref>

In September 2024, as he had already started playing with the reserve, he signed his first professional contract with Boca Juniors.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-03-04 |title=La historia de Tomás Aranda, "el mejor jugador de las inferiores" que la rompió ante Lanús |url=https://www.tycsports.com/boca-juniors/tomas-aranda-mejor-jugador-inferiores-boca-titular-platense-id712845.html |access-date=2026-04-08 |website=TyC Sports |language=es-AR}}</ref> The following year he led the reserve to a win in the [[Torneo de Reserva (Argentina)|Torneo de Reserva]] and the Trofeo de Campeones.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-12-11 |title=Boca venció a Vélez y se consagró campeón del Trofeo de Campeones de Reserva: reviví lo mejor |url=https://www.tycsports.com/boca-juniors/boca-vs-velez-por-el-trofeo-de-campeones-de-reserva-hora-formaciones-y-tv-en-vivo-id703458.html |access-date=2026-04-08 |website=TyC Sports |language=es-AR}}</ref>

Aranda made his professional debut with Boca Juniors in a 2–1 [[2026 AFA Liga Profesional de Fútbol|Primera División]] loss to [[Estudiantes de La Plata]] on 28 January 2026.<ref name=udr/><ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-01-28 |title=Boca Juniors perdió 2-1 contra Estudiantes en La Plata por la segunda fecha del Torneo Apertura |url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes/2026/01/28/boca-juniors-tendra-una-prueba-de-riesgo-en-la-plata-ante-estudiantes-hora-tv-y-formaciones/ |access-date=2026-04-08 |website=infobae |language=es-AR}}</ref>

== International career ==
Aranda is a youth international for Argentina, having first been called to the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|under-20 team]] in March 2026.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-03-22 |title=Tomás Aranda a la Selección Argentina: del ascenso meteórico en Boca al llamado a la Sub 20 |url=https://www.ole.com.ar/boca-juniors/tomas-aranda-seleccion-argentina-ascenso-meteorico-boca-llamado-sub-20_0_TT4KacXYUo.html |access-date=2026-04-08 |website=Olé |language=es-AR}}</ref> He made his debut on 27 March, starting in a friendly against the [[United States men's national under-20 soccer team|United States]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-03-27 |title=Argentina Sub 20 cayó 0-3 con Estados Unidos en el predio de Ezeiza ante los ojos de Scaloni, Messi y más jugadores de la Selección |url=https://www.clarin.com/deportes/amistoso-sub-20-argentina-enfrenta-estados-unidos-predio-ezeiza-tomas-aranda-ian-subiabre-titulares_0_NBE4iZqOGP.html |access-date=2026-04-08 |website=Clarín |language=es}}</ref>

